[00:07.261]Moon's up high, shining wide.
[00:08.979]Counting sheep on my bed.
[00:11.435]Who's still awake? Tossing and turning?
[00:14.372]Little lamb, wool so white.
[00:16.427]Why're you hiding from the rest?
[00:18.859]Glow in the dark, come when the sun sets
[00:22.227]Ayayayaya Ayayayayayaya
[00:26.397]I ring my bell, I ring my bell
[00:29.587]Meadow grass swaying slow. Gentle green with hints of gold.
[00:33.539]The twilight paints the end of summer
[00:36.531]Electric sheep, do you dream,
[00:38.659]of machines in your sleep?
[00:41.067]Or do you dream of running far and free
[00:44.651]Ayayayaya Ayayayayayaya
[00:48.515]I ring my bell, I ring my bell
